### Scripting with solidity

- What it is: Write deployment logic in Solidity and run on Foundry's fast EVM backend with dry‑run simulation. Preferable to `forge create` for multi‑step, declarative deploys.[[1]](https://getfoundry.sh/guides/scripting-with-solidity#vocs-content)[[2]](https://getfoundry.sh/forge/reference/create)
- How `forge script` runs (4 phases):
    1. Local simulation collects transactions triggered during `vm.broadcast` or `vm.startBroadcast` calls.
    2. On‑chain simulation (if RPC/fork URL provided) replays those txns.
    3. Broadcasting with `--broadcast` sends the collected txns if sims succeeded.
    4. Verification with `--verify` attempts Etherscan verification if API key present. Use `--resume` to retry timed‑out txns. Results may differ from sim due to MEV/front‑running.[[1]](https://getfoundry.sh/guides/scripting-with-solidity#vocs-content)
- Project setup: `forge init Counter` then `forge build`.
- Prereqs for Sepolia: RPC URL (Chainlist/Alchemy/Infura), one‑time deployer key `cast wallet new`, fund with faucet ETH, Etherscan API key.[[3]](https://chainlist.org/chain/11155111)[[4]](https://www.alchemy.com/)[[5]](https://www.infura.io/)[[6]](https://sepolia-faucet.pk910.de/)[[7]](https://sepoliafaucet.com/)[[8]](https://faucet.quicknode.com/ethereum/sepolia)[[9]](https://faucet.chainstack.com/)[[10]](https://docs.etherscan.io/getting-started/viewing-api-usage-statistics)
- Env and config: Add `.env` values `SEPOLIA_RPC_URL` and `ETHERSCAN_API_KEY`. In `foundry.toml` add:
    
    [rpc_endpoints] sepolia = "${SEPOLIA_RPC_URL}"
    
    [etherscan] sepolia = { key = "${ETHERSCAN_API_KEY}" }.[[11]](https://getfoundry.sh/reference/cheatcodes/rpc)
    
- Writing the script: `CounterScript` inherits `Script`; in `run()` call `vm.startBroadcast()`, deploy `new Counter()`, then `vm.stopBroadcast()`. Consider the Config contract pattern for complex, multi‑chain orchestration.[[12]](https://getfoundry.sh/guides/scripting-with-config)
- Deploy and verify to Sepolia:
    - `source .env`
    - `forge script --chain sepolia script/Counter.s.sol:CounterScript --rpc-url $SEPOLIA_RPC_URL --broadcast --verify -vvvv --interactives 1`
    - Enter private key when prompted; prefer hardware wallet or protected keystore for anything beyond local/test.[[13]](https://getfoundry.sh/guides/best-practices/key-management)
- Outputs: Forge prints traces, tx hashes, contract address, and verification status; artifacts saved under `broadcast/.../run-latest.json`.
- Local testing with Anvil: run `anvil`, then `forge script script/Counter.s.sol:CounterScript --fork-url http://localhost:8545 --broadcast --interactives 1` and use a listed private key. Artifacts saved under the 31337 folder.
- Tip: Avoid embedding secrets in commands; load from env. Use interactive prompts or external wallets for production.
- TLDR: forge script script/DeploySimpleStorage.s.sol --rpc-url [http://127.0.0.1:8545](http://127.0.0.1:8545/) --broadcast --private-key 0xac0974bec39a17e36ba4a6b4d238ff944bacb478cbed5efcae784d7bf4f2ff80

