### Never use a .env file

Instead of an .env file, encrypt your key using this bash command:

- `cast wallet import <KEY_NAME> --interactive`
- This opens a write-only prompt to enter the private key you want to encrypt and the password to protect it.
- An address will be returned. As explained in the fundamentals, this address is generated from the public key, which is derived from the private key you just encrypted. It is deterministic from Anvil's default mnemonic.
- After you get your address, you can deploy safely using:
    - `forge script script/<SCRIPT_NAME> --rpc-url <RPC_URL> --account <KEY_NAME> --sender <ADDRESS> --broadcast -vvv`
- BE SURE TO REMOVE THE PRIVATE KEY FROM YOUR SHELL HISTORY IF YOU TYPED IT.
